cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.DS

This paper deals with reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The focus is on input-driven environments, which suggests a connection to robotics and control (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY). The use of policy gradient methods and meta-learning suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the experimental results cover a range of environments, which suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) for efficient implementation and evaluation.
